## Overview

TaskSyncPro is designed for organizations that need consistent task workflows, structured ownership, and traceable activity across teams. It combines rigorous validation rules with a pragmatic REST API for operational use cases and educational demonstration.

## Architecture

The solution follows a clean 3‑tier architecture:

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    Client[Client Apps] --> API[API Layer]
    API --> BLL[BLL Services]
    BLL --> DAL[DAL Repositories]
    DAL --> DB[(SQL Server)]
```

Entity relationships (simplified):

```mermaid
erDiagram
    ROLE ||--o{ USER : has
    USER ||--o| EMPLOYEE : links
    TEAM ||--o{ EMPLOYEE : contains
    USER ||--o{ TASK : creates
    EMPLOYEE ||--o{ TASK : assigned
    TASK ||--o| BILLINGRECORD : billed
    TASK ||--o{ TASKLOG : logs
```

## Technology Stack

- .NET 10.0, ASP.NET Core 10.0, C# 12
- Entity Framework Core 9.0.11 with SQL Server
- AutoMapper 14.0.0, Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi 10.0.1, System.Net.Mail
- Repository + Factory patterns, DTO-based contracts, Dependency Injection

---

## Setup

### Prerequisites

- [.NET 10 SDK](https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download)
- SQL Server (Express, Developer, or Enterprise)

### Configuration

Update the connection string in [API/appsettings.json](API/appsettings.json).

### Apply Migrations

```bash
dotnet ef database update --project DAL --startup-project API
```

### Install & Build

```bash
dotnet restore
dotnet build
```

### Run

```bash
dotnet run --project API
```

API URLs:

- HTTPS: `https://localhost:5001`
- HTTP: `http://localhost:5000`
- OpenAPI: `https://localhost:5001/openapi/v1.json` (Development)

### Email Credentials (Optional)

Credential delivery uses SMTP in [BLL/Helpers/EmailService.cs](BLL/Helpers/EmailService.cs). Replace the sender address and app password before production use.

